The Board shall report to the Governor and, subject to § 2-1246 of the State Government Article, to the General Assembly before November 1 of each year on:
The financial status of the Program for the preceding fiscal year, including the amount of grants encumbered and disbursed;
The number of applications received;
The number and location of Rural Legacy Areas designated; and
The Program's progress in contributing to land preservation efforts.
